---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { DATA_CONTROLLER, POLICY_LAST_UPDATED, POLICY_VERSION } from '../../data/legal';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — Prismatica" description="Prismatica privacy policy and GDPR information.">
	<main class="legal-page section-shell">
		<a href="/" class="legal-page__back">← Back to Prismatica</a>
		<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
		<p><strong>Policy version:</strong> {POLICY_VERSION} · <strong>Last updated:</strong> {POLICY_LAST_UPDATED}</p>

		<section>
			<h2>Data controller</h2>
			<p>{DATA_CONTROLLER.name}, {DATA_CONTROLLER.address}, is the data controller for Prismatica.</p>
			<p>Privacy contact: <a href={`mailto:${DATA_CONTROLLER.email}`}>{DATA_CONTROLLER.email}</a>. DPO contact: <a href={`mailto:${DATA_CONTROLLER.dpoEmail}`}>{DATA_CONTROLLER.dpoEmail}</a>.</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Data we collect and why</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Account data:</strong> email, username, password hash and account timestamps. Legal basis: contract and legitimate interest in account security.</li>
				<li><strong>Optional profile data:</strong> first name, last name, avatar URL and biography. Legal basis: consent or contract when the user chooses to provide it.</li>
				<li><strong>Preferences:</strong> theme, notification settings and newsletter consent. Legal basis: contract for service preferences and consent for optional communications.</li>
				<li><strong>Security logs:</strong> activity type, IP address, browser or device strings, and timestamps. IP addresses are personal data. Legal basis: legitimate interest in security, fraud prevention and troubleshooting.</li>
				<li><strong>Tokens and sessions:</strong> reset tokens, verification tokens and session identifiers. Legal basis: contract and legitimate interest in secure authentication.</li>
			</ul>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Retention</h2>
			<p>Account data is kept for the account lifetime and anonymised or deleted after a verified erasure request, unless a legal hold applies. Security activity logs are retained for a maximum of 13 months in line with CNIL guidance. Expired session and reset tokens are purged as soon as operationally possible.</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Recipients and processors</h2>
			<p>Data is processed by the application infrastructure and hosting processors needed to operate the service. We do not sell personal data. Production processors must be documented in the processing register before launch.</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>International transfers</h2>
			<p>The local development stack does not intentionally transfer personal data outside the EU. Production deployments must use EU/EEA hosting or document appropriate transfer safeguards before processing EU residents' data.</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Your rights</h2>
			<p>You can exercise your rights of access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability and objection under GDPR Articles 15 to 21. You can also withdraw consent at any time where processing is based on consent.</p>
			<p>Use the <a href="/legal/data-rights/">Data Rights form</a> or contact <a href={`mailto:${DATA_CONTROLLER.email}`}>{DATA_CONTROLLER.email}</a>.</p>
			<p>You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the CNIL: <a href="https://www.cnil.fr/fr/plaintes" rel="noreferrer">https://www.cnil.fr/fr/plaintes</a>.</p>
		</section>

		<section>
			<h2>Cookies and local storage</h2>
			<p>Strictly necessary local preferences are used for theme, motion and consent records. Optional analytics, marketing or newsletter tracking must not load unless consent is granted. See the <a href="/legal/cookies/">Cookie Policy</a>.</p>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>
